Step 1: Identify the total revenue amount from the income statement.
• Total Revenue = 5,565,589.48

Step 2: Find the total assets at the beginning and at the end from the balance sheet.
• Beginning Total Assets = 13,000,000.00  
• Ending Total Assets = 14,823,650.85

Step 3: Calculate the average total assets.
• Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
• Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 14,823,650.85) / 2 = 27,823,650.85 / 2  
• Average Total Assets ≈ 13,911,825.43

Step 4: Compute the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio = 5,565,589.48 / 13,911,825.43 ≈ 0.40

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.40"
  }
}
